abstract_ssm: Malcolm Goldstein is a composer and violinist primarily concerned with structured improvisation and a unique style which he calls "soundings." He writes graphic scores which combine elements of standard musical notation, calligraphy, written instructions, and collage. Goldstein has collaborated with many dancers, writers, and musicians, most frequently with Philip Corner and Allison Knowles. The Malcolm Goldstein Papers contais scores, documentation of performances, writings, publicity, and administrative documents relating to Goldstein's work as composer, musician, collaborator, writer, curator, and professor.
